<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E60FFEE48F75126FD18F8B2" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="007606418E60FFEE48F75126FD18F8B2" blockId="46.[151,1436,1510,2003]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E60FFEE48F75126FEE4F9D3" bold="true" box="[199,321,1546,1571]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E60FFEE49795127FE38F9D3" box="[329,413,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Female</emphasis>
: fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE4A7D5126FD7BF9D2" box="[589,734,1546,1570]" captionStart="PLATE 13" captionStartId="50.[151,233,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[303,1298,205,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-49@50.[268,1319,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="PLATE 13. Conganteon richardsi, holotype (from Olmi 1984). A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.8 mm. C. Chela. Scale bar 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278414/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plate 13A, B</figureCitation>
); occipital carina complete; mandible quadridentate, with one intermediate rudimentary tooth (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE4A375102FDC3F9B6" box="[519,614,1582,1606]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,233,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[163,1415,270,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-69@10.[151,1436,253,1777]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="PLATE 3. A–C, F, G. Males. D, E. Mandibles. A. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. B. Fiorianteon sp. Length 3.8 mm. C. Dryinus sp. Length 3.7 mm. D. Anteon sp., Female. E. Dryinidae. F. Thaumatodryinus sp. Length 1.9 mm. G. Anteon sp. Length 2.5 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278380/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plate 3E</figureCitation>
); antenna without rhinaria; palpal formula 5/3 or 6/3; pronotal tubercles present; fore wing with two cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal and median) (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE4C7C517EFB78F99A" box="[1100,1245,1618,1642]" captionStart="PLATE 13" captionStartId="50.[151,233,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[303,1298,205,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-49@50.[268,1319,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="PLATE 13. Conganteon richardsi, holotype (from Olmi 1984). A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.8 mm. C. Chela. Scale bar 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278414/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plate 13A, B</figureCitation>
); fore wing with stigmal vein and pterostigma (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE49DA515AFDDCF97E" box="[490,633,1654,1678]" captionStart="PLATE 13" captionStartId="50.[151,233,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[303,1298,205,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-49@50.[268,1319,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="PLATE 13. Conganteon richardsi, holotype (from Olmi 1984). A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.8 mm. C. Chela. Scale bar 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278414/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plate 13A, B</figureCitation>
); distal part of stigmal vein longer than proximal part (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE4CEF515AFAFCF97E" box="[1247,1369,1654,1678]" captionStart="PLATE 12" captionStartId="47.[151,233,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[165,1419,217,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-90@47.[151,1436,195,1898]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="PLATE 12. A, B. Conganteon gigas, holotype (from Xu &amp; He, 1998b). C–E. C. nepalense. A. Chela. B. Fore wing. C. Chela of female from India (from Olmi 1987a). D. Genitalia of holotype (from Olmi 1984). E. Holotype (from Olmi 1984). Length 1.9 mm. Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.68 mm for B, 0.13 mm for C and 0.21 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278410/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plates 12B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE4D55515AFF0FF942" captionStart="PLATE 13" captionStartId="50.[151,233,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[303,1298,205,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-49@50.[268,1319,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="PLATE 13. Conganteon richardsi, holotype (from Olmi 1984). A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.8 mm. C. Chela. Scale bar 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278414/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">13A, B</figureCitation>
); protarsus chelate (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE49A651B6FD8EF942" box="[406,555,1690,1714]" captionStart="PLATE 13" captionStartId="50.[151,233,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[303,1298,205,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-49@50.[268,1319,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="PLATE 13. Conganteon richardsi, holotype (from Olmi 1984). A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.8 mm. C. Chela. Scale bar 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278414/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plate 13A, B</figureCitation>
); chela with a rudimentary claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE4B8451B6FB94F942" box="[948,1073,1690,1714]" captionStart="PLATE 13" captionStartId="50.[151,233,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[303,1298,205,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-49@50.[268,1319,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="PLATE 13. Conganteon richardsi, holotype (from Olmi 1984). A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.8 mm. C. Chela. Scale bar 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278414/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plates 13C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE4C0F51B6FBD6F942" box="[1087,1139,1690,1714]" captionStart="PLATE 14" captionStartId="52.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[186,1399,215,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-105@52.[166,1421,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="PLATE 14. A, C. Chelae, holotypes. B, D–F. Male genitalia. A. Conganteon taiwanense (from Olmi 1991). B. C. taiwanense from China, Nanling (from Olmi 1995a). C. Fiorianteon choui (from Olmi 1995a). D. F.choui, paratype (from Olmi 1995a). E. F.choui from China, Nanling. F. F. junonium, holotype (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.09 mm for A, 0.30 mm for B, 0.20 mm for C, 0.24 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and 0.31 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278418/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">14A</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/1/2. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E60FFEE4D6B51B7FA31F943" box="[1371,1428,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Male</emphasis>
: fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE490B5192FE0CF926" box="[315,425,1726,1750]" captionStart="PLATE 12" captionStartId="47.[151,233,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[165,1419,217,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-90@47.[151,1436,195,1898]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="PLATE 12. A, B. Conganteon gigas, holotype (from Xu &amp; He, 1998b). C–E. C. nepalense. A. Chela. B. Fore wing. C. Chela of female from India (from Olmi 1987a). D. Genitalia of holotype (from Olmi 1984). E. Holotype (from Olmi 1984). Length 1.9 mm. Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.68 mm for B, 0.13 mm for C and 0.21 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278410/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plate 12E</figureCitation>
); occipital carina complete; mandible quadridentate, with one intermediate rudimentary tooth (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE48D451CEFEE3F90A" box="[228,326,1762,1786]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,233,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[163,1415,270,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-69@10.[151,1436,253,1777]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="PLATE 3. A–C, F, G. Males. D, E. Mandibles. A. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. B. Fiorianteon sp. Length 3.8 mm. C. Dryinus sp. Length 3.7 mm. D. Anteon sp., Female. E. Dryinidae. F. Thaumatodryinus sp. Length 1.9 mm. G. Anteon sp. Length 2.5 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278380/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plate 3E</figureCitation>
); palpal formula 5/3 or 6/3; fore wing with two cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal and median) (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE4935502AFED6F8EE" box="[261,371,1798,1822]" captionStart="PLATE 12" captionStartId="47.[151,233,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[165,1419,217,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-90@47.[151,1436,195,1898]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="PLATE 12. A, B. Conganteon gigas, holotype (from Xu &amp; He, 1998b). C–E. C. nepalense. A. Chela. B. Fore wing. C. Chela of female from India (from Olmi 1987a). D. Genitalia of holotype (from Olmi 1984). E. Holotype (from Olmi 1984). Length 1.9 mm. Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.68 mm for B, 0.13 mm for C and 0.21 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278410/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plate 12E</figureCitation>
