<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE4BAC502AFBAFF8EE" box="[924,1034,1798,1822]" captionStart="PLATE 12" captionStartId="47.[151,233,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[165,1419,217,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-90@47.[151,1436,195,1898]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="PLATE 12. A, B. Conganteon gigas, holotype (from Xu &amp; He, 1998b). C–E. C. nepalense. A. Chela. B. Fore wing. C. Chela of female from India (from Olmi 1987a). D. Genitalia of holotype (from Olmi 1984). E. Holotype (from Olmi 1984). Length 1.9 mm. Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.68 mm for B, 0.13 mm for C and 0.21 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278410/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plate 12E</figureCitation>
); distal part of stigmal vein longer than proximal part (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E60FFEE49465006FE44F8B2" box="[374,481,1834,1858]" captionStart="PLATE 12" captionStartId="47.[151,233,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[165,1419,217,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-90@47.[151,1436,195,1898]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="PLATE 12. A, B. Conganteon gigas, holotype (from Xu &amp; He, 1998b). C–E. C. nepalense. A. Chela. B. Fore wing. C. Chela of female from India (from Olmi 1987a). D. Genitalia of holotype (from Olmi 1984). E. Holotype (from Olmi 1984). Length 1.9 mm. Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.68 mm for B, 0.13 mm for C and 0.21 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278410/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Plate 12E</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
